      "message": "Jae, can you please read and audit the LLM output before you post it?  I don\u0027t want to argue with a robot, or I can get my robot to argue with your robot.\n\n    D-Bus get-property latency  count\u003d50             count\u003d50\n                                min\u003d20000 us         min\u003d20000 us\n                                avg\u003d29200 us         avg\u003d30400 us\n                                p50\u003d30000 us         p50\u003d30000 us\n                                p90\u003d40000 us         p90\u003d40000 us\n                                p99\u003d40000 us         p99\u003d40000 us\n                                max\u003d40000 us         max\u003d40000 us\n                                \nAverage for uring based one appears to be marginally faster, so I\u0027m not sure what we\u0027re doing here.\n\n\"However, based on these results, I don\u0027t see any\nsignificant performance difference or regression between using io_uring and\nio_uring + epoll.\"\n\nSo lets keep the uring implementation and abandon this patch?",
