      "side": 1,
      "message": "Brad, I\u0027m a little confused.  From my perspective this isn\u0027t giving flexibility, it\u0027s just hardcoding a different set of tradeoffs.  Before we do that, I\u0027d like at least SOME indication in the commit message of why we did it so that in 2 months when someone proposes the opposite, I can point to the problem being solved.\n\n\u003e I can\u0027t imagine why using io_uring over epoll for non-file IO would have any meaningful performance impact\n\nExactly...... I can\u0027t either, and I don\u0027t think the commit message give adequate justification for why we should change.\n\nOne downside would be that we\u0027re chaining reactors, adding extra sys calls to add the uring into an epoll.  If we find that\u0027s truly faster, I\u0027m open to that, but we should back that up with at least a little load testing.",
